Nissan Motor Co. Chief Executive
 Carlos Ghosn  will visit  Turkey  in July for talks on building a
car plant in the country with the business group Oyak,  Hurriyet 
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Ghosn, who will be in Istanbul on July 5, will ask the
government for incentives for the plant, the newspaper said. One
possible location for the factory is Iskenderun on Turkeyâ€™s
southern coast, the newspaper said.  Renault SA (RNO) , which makes cars in Turkey with the army
pension fund Oyak group, will join the project, Hurriyet said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
